        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        Amazon Customer
        5 Stars
        Follow directions to the letter
        The directions for this product are very specific, i.e. if you mess something up, the directions recommend you do it again. You need to wait at least 48 hours before last ejaculation to do the test. It did not explain why but Im guessing its due to the number of sperm in the semen after multiple ejaculations.You need to get ALL the sperm in the cup. This needs to be done because the average volume of sperm per ejaculation is only about one teaspoonful, and thats not a lot. Theres a little syringe you have to suck it up in and its aggravating because of the little amount of sperm in the cup.Our result had a test line along with the control line but it wasnt as dark as the control line. Still, this should be considered a positive result. I believe that as long as there is a test line that shows up, the result is positive and within the average results for fertile men. Ive always been confused about how these tests work. Its similar to pregnancy and ovulation tests. The test line is never as dark as the control line on pregnancy tests but its still positive if a test line appears, so I believe its the same for this test.Overall, the product works if you follow directions.

        DaveandMickayla
        5.0 out of 5 stars Nice quick do-it-yourself test
        Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2014
        Verified Purchase
        It's a little pricey, but overall I'm pretty satisfied with the product (and that I seemingly passed the test). It has clear, easy-to-follow instructions, and doesn't take much time at all - 7 minutes for results, about an hour total time. Read the instructions a few times and then just start checking them off as you go.

        I got a head-start because the company has a copy of the instructions on their website for download, which is nice. I also found a coupon for a $10 rebate if purchased during the 2014 calendar year - I'm not sure if online/amazon purchases count (it said to include a copy of the "cash register receipt", which I obviously don't have from amazon, just a printed copy of my order/invoice), but I would hope so. If I think of it, I'll follow up if I get a rebate check in 4-6 weeks!

        I was a little nervous in the 2 days leading up to the test, but there was definitely an ominous two-minute wait period towards the end of the test, plus the final moment as you're putting 6 drops into the test that will determine the fate of your unborn children. Steel yourself.

        My line was faint, but it was definitely there. It made me wonder if somebody with superman sperm would have a super-dark line. Does anybody know if a darker Test line equates to a higher sperm count by comparison to a really faint line? Meaning in theory a dark line might be 50 million and a faint line would be the 20 million base?

        We haven't started trying to get pregnant yet, I was just doing this test because my brother is having issues conceiving and apparently has some issues with his swimmers and got me a little paranoid. I would definitely recommend this as a quick way to find out something, though I also would suggest you talk to your doctor and see a urologist if you're seriously concerned and need help. It's nothing to be embarrassed about - get as much info as you can so you figure it out for your family's future. Good luck!
